<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="@color/bgColor"
    android:scrollbars="none"
    android:fitsSystemWindows="true">

    <LinearLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:orientation="vertical">

        <!-- 🔴 PREMIUM HEADER -->
        <RelativeLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="150dp"
            android:background="@drawable/red_header_bg"
            android:padding="24dp">

            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical">

                <ImageView
                    android:id="@+id/btnBack"
                    android:layout_width="40dp"
                    android:layout_height="40dp"
                    android:padding="9dp"
                    android:src="@drawable/rs_back"
                    app:tint="@color/white"
                    android:background="?attr/selectableItemBackgroundBorderless"/>

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:text="Health &amp; Wellness"
                    android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"
                    android:textColor="@android:color/white"
                    android:textSize="26sp"
                    android:textStyle="bold"
                    android:letterSpacing="0.01"/>
            </LinearLayout>
        </RelativeLayout>

        <!-- 📝 MAIN CONTENT CARD -->
        <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginTop="-45dp"
            android:layout_marginStart="20dp"
            android:layout_marginEnd="20dp"
            android:layout_marginBottom="25dp"
            app:cardCornerRadius="30dp"
            app:cardElevation="15dp"
            app:cardBackgroundColor="@color/cardColor">

            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:orientation="vertical"
                android:padding="22dp">

                <TextView
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:fontFamily="sans-serif-black"
                    android:text="Expert Health Advice 🩺"
                    android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                    android:textSize="22sp"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"/>

                <!-- 1. Blood Donation -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/blood_donation_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="Blood Donation Guide"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv1"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="❤️ Save Lives, Be a Hero. Blood donation is a noble act that can save up to three lives with a single donation. Regular donation not only helps the community but also benefits the donor's health by reducing excess iron levels in the blood, which can lower the risk of heart disease and liver damage. Before donating, ensure you are well-rested, hydrated, and have had a light, healthy meal. Avoid fatty foods and alcohol at least 24 hours prior. After the procedure, keep yourself hydrated and avoid heavy physical activity for the rest of the day. Your single contribution acts as a lifeline for patients undergoing surgeries, cancer treatments, or recovering from chronic illnesses. Remember, your blood can be the reason someone else celebrates another birthday. Stay healthy to keep others alive! Your donation matters more than you can imagine."
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn1"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

                <!-- 2. Addiction -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/addiction_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="Overcoming Addiction"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv2"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="⚠️ Break Free, Live Better. Addiction is a complex condition that affects the brain and behavior, making it difficult to control the use of legal or illegal substances. Whether it is tobacco, alcohol, or other substances, the path to recovery starts with acceptance and a strong will to change. Chronic addiction can lead to severe health issues, including respiratory failure, cardiovascular disease, and mental health disorders like anxiety and depression. To start your journey, identify your triggers—stress, peer pressure, or specific environments. Surround yourself with supportive family and friends, and don't hesitate to seek professional counseling or join support groups. Replacing harmful habits with productive activities like exercise, meditation, or hobbies can significantly rewire your brain's reward system. Healing takes time, but every day without the substance is a victory for your future and your loved ones. You are stronger than your addiction!"
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn2"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

                <!-- 3. Heart Health -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/heart_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="Heart Health Secrets"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv3"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="💓 Keep Your Heart Strong. Your heart is the engine of your body, pumping life-sustaining blood to every cell. Maintaining its health requires a combination of a balanced diet, regular physical activity, and stress management. Incorporate heart-healthy fats found in olive oil, nuts, and fish, and reduce intake of processed sugars and trans-fats that clog arteries. Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise like brisk walking or swimming daily to strengthen the cardiac muscles. High blood pressure and high cholesterol are silent killers, so regular screenings are crucial. Additionally, managing stress through deep breathing or yoga can prevent long-term damage to the heart's rhythm. Quality sleep of 7-8 hours is also vital for the heart to repair itself. A healthy heart isn't just about living longer; it's about having the energy to enjoy every moment of your life to the fullest. Take care of your heart, and it will take care of you! Healthy habits today mean a stronger heart tomorrow."
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn3"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

                <!-- 4. Hydration -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/hydration_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="The Power of Hydration"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv4"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="🌊 Stay Hydrated, Stay Energized. Water is fundamental to every biological process in the human body, from regulating temperature to lubricating joints and transporting nutrients. Dehydration can lead to fatigue, headaches, poor concentration, and even kidney problems. For blood donors, hydration is especially critical because it helps maintain blood volume and prevents dizziness post-donation. Aim to drink at least 8-10 glasses of water daily, and more if you are physically active or living in a hot climate. Don't wait until you feel thirsty; thirst is a late sign of dehydration. Incorporate water-rich foods like cucumbers, watermelons, and oranges into your diet. Limit excessive intake of caffeine and soda, which can act as diuretics. A well-hydrated body ensures glowing skin, improved digestion, and a faster metabolism. Make carrying a water bottle a habit, and your body will thank you with sustained energy levels throughout the day! Water is the elixir of life, so drink up!"
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn4"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

                <!-- 5. Nutrition -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:layout_marginBottom="24dp">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/food_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="Balanced Nutrition"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv5"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="🥗 Fuel Your Body Right. A balanced diet is the cornerstone of good health and a robust immune system. Consuming a variety of whole foods, including colorful vegetables, fruits, lean proteins, and whole grains, provides the essential vitamins and minerals your body needs to function optimally. Iron-rich foods like spinach, beans, and lean meats are particularly important for blood donors to help replenish hemoglobin levels quickly. Avoid excessive intake of highly processed foods, which are often high in sodium, unhealthy fats, and added sugars that can lead to weight gain and chronic diseases like diabetes. Fiber-dense foods aid in digestion and help maintain a healthy weight. Planning your meals ahead of time can prevent impulsive, unhealthy eating choices. Remember, what you put on your plate today determines your energy levels and long-term health. Nutrition isn't about restriction; it's about nourishing your cells and thriving. Treat your body like a temple, and it will serve you well for years to come! Eat well to live well."
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn5"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

                <!-- 6. Exercise -->
                <LinearLayout
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                    android:orientation="vertical">

                    <LinearLayout
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:orientation="horizontal">
                        <ImageView
                            android:layout_width="36dp"
                            android:layout_height="36dp"
                            android:src="@drawable/exercise_healthtips" />
                        <TextView
                            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                            android:layout_marginStart="12dp"
                            android:text="Stay Active Daily"
                            android:textColor="@color/textPrimary"
                            android:textSize="18sp"
                            android:textStyle="bold" />
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv6"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="12dp"
                        android:ellipsize="end"
                        android:lineSpacingExtra="6dp"
                        android:maxLines="3"
                        android:text="🏃‍♂️ Move More, Live Longer. Regular physical activity is one of the most important things you can do for your health. Exercise helps control weight, reduces the risk of cardiovascular diseases, and strengthens your bones and muscles. Beyond physical benefits, staying active is a powerful tool for improving mental health by reducing anxiety and boosting mood through the release of endorphins. You don't need a gym membership to stay fit; simple activities like taking the stairs, gardening, or a daily 30-minute walk can make a massive difference over time. Consistency is key—find an activity you enjoy, whether it's dancing, cycling, or yoga, and make it a non-negotiable part of your routine. Exercise also improves sleep quality and increases your overall energy levels, making you more productive throughout the day. Listen to your body and start at your own pace, gradually increasing intensity as you get stronger. Every step you take is a step toward a healthier, happier you. Don't find time to exercise; make time for it! Your future self will thank you for the effort you put in today."
                        android:textColor="@color/textSecondary"
                        android:textSize="14sp" />

                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn6"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="32dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="end"
                        android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                        android:backgroundTint="@color/active_requests_bg"
                        android:insetTop="0dp"
                        android:insetBottom="0dp"
                        android:paddingStart="16dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="16dp"
                        android:text="Read More"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:textColor="@color/active_requests_text"
                        android:textSize="12sp"
                        app:cornerRadius="16dp" />
                </LinearLayout>

            </LinearLayout>
        </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>

    </LinearLayout>
</androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
